contentrichtext.text: '''Tethys''' can refer to: * [[Tethys (mythology)]], a Titaness in Greek mythology * [[Tethys (moon)]], a natural satellite of Saturn * [[Tethys Ocean]], a Mesozoic-era ocean between the continents of Gondwana and Laurasia ** [[Prototethys]] Ocean (c. 550–330 [[Megaannum|Ma]]) ** [[Paleotethys]] Ocean (c. 445–75 Ma) ** [[Neotethys]] Ocean (c. 300–100 Ma) ** Alpine Tethys Sea (c. 175–30 Ma) or [[Paratethys]] Sea (isolated after 34 Ma); today's [[Black Sea]], [[Caspian Sea]], and [[Aral Sea]] are remnants of the Paratethys Sea * [[Tethys (gastropod)|''Tethys'' (gastropod)]], genus of gastropods in the family [[Tethydidae]] ==See also== *[[Thetis (disambiguation)|Thetis]] {{disambig}}
